10 Tally up all of the people by race.






hint





hint: Make a count() of race





Show the code
sqf_2021 |&gt;
  select(SUSPECT_SEX, SUSPECT_RACE_DESCRIPTION, SUSPECT_REPORTED_AGE)|&gt;
  rename("sex" = "SUSPECT_SEX",
         "race" = "SUSPECT_RACE_DESCRIPTION",
         "age" = "SUSPECT_REPORTED_AGE") |&gt;
  count(race)

11 Make your variables more readable






hint





hint: rename the column n to total





Show the code
sqf_2021 |&gt;
  select(SUSPECT_SEX, SUSPECT_RACE_DESCRIPTION, SUSPECT_REPORTED_AGE)|&gt;
  rename("sex" = "SUSPECT_SEX",
         "race" = "SUSPECT_RACE_DESCRIPTION",
         "age" = "SUSPECT_REPORTED_AGE") |&gt;
  count(race) |&gt;
  rename("total" = "n")

12 Add in the percent colummn






hint





hint: Add a percentage column with mutate()





Show the code
sqf_2021 |&gt;
  select(SUSPECT_SEX, SUSPECT_RACE_DESCRIPTION, SUSPECT_REPORTED_AGE)|&gt;
  rename("sex" = "SUSPECT_SEX",
         "race" = "SUSPECT_RACE_DESCRIPTION",
         "age" = "SUSPECT_REPORTED_AGE") |&gt;
  count(race) |&gt;
  rename("total" = "n") |&gt;
  mutate(percentage = total/sum(total) * 100)

13 Order the percent column






hint





hint: arrange() the percent column so that they are in order.





Show the code
sqf_2021 |&gt;
  select(SUSPECT_SEX, SUSPECT_RACE_DESCRIPTION, SUSPECT_REPORTED_AGE)|&gt;
  rename("sex" = "SUSPECT_SEX",
         "race" = "SUSPECT_RACE_DESCRIPTION",
         "age" = "SUSPECT_REPORTED_AGE") |&gt;
  count(race) |&gt;
  rename("total" = "n") |&gt;
  mutate(percentage = total/sum(total) * 100) |&gt;
  arrange(percentage)
